body:
A score expression represents the relevance score, which is the
score MongoDB Search assigns documents based on relevance, of the query.
It is the same as the current score of the document. It must
include the following option:

| Option | Type   | Description                                                     |
| ------ | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| score  | string | Value of relevance score of the query. Value must be relevance. |

> **Example:**&#x20;
>
> ```sh
> {
>   "function": {
>     "score": "relevance"
>   }
> }
> ```
